data.description:
***2.25% assumable VA loan is available regardless of veteran status.***
Separate guest suite can be offered as revenue generating. 
See more details at https://141ridgewood.wixsite.com/141_ridgewood
Gracious 4/4.5 two story home on a half-acre site. Located in a highly desirable neighborhood just minutes from downtown Brevard. The warm, inviting kitchen has been completely renovated in 2023 with custom wood cabinets, quartz countertops, double ovens, and extra-large pantry. Flooring on the main level is solid oak plank installed in 2023. The front entry as well as windows in the kitchen and breakfast nook are also new in 2023. 
The first floor includes living, dining, half-bath, laundry room, and flexible spaces for music and art, working out, or as a maker space. These creative and work spaces have several built in storage areas and are nearly indestructible, with concrete floors that aren't bothered by spilled paint. The living room features a wood-burning stove and built-in shelving. 
The enclosed screen porch/sunroom has removable insulated poly panels for year-round enjoyment. The yard and garden are filled with low-maintenance perennials and the wooded area surrounding the home makes this half-acre site feel like even more. The home is located in a park-like neighborhood that's just one mile from the high school and across from the Brevard Health and Racquet Club.

The property includes a separate guest house attached to the single-car garage. This separate structure includes a bedroom, closet, and full bathroom. The suite has also been used as a second office. When briefly offered on a short-term rental platform, the guest suite quickly booked up and could easily be revenue generating.
Systems include a gas furnace on the main floor and heat pump on the second floor as well as a wood burning stove insert in the fireplace. The guest apartment has a mini-split heat pump and radiant heating in the ceiling. The home offices have gigabit internet service available and cell reception.

The exterior is brick and wood siding with a composite roof. Extensive storage is available in the humidity-controlled, encapsulated crawl space below the house. The wrap-around driveway and front parking space offer plenty of room to welcome family and friends. An additional gravel parking area is large enough to accommodate a 35' RV or boat. Or both! 
The home is currently financed with a VA loan. One benefit of VA loans is that they are assumable. A non-veteran buyer (as well as a veteran buyer, of course) can access the financing already in place at an incredible 2.25% mortgage rate.
data.whatILove:
The best thing about this home is the flexibility it provides. This includes multiple office options for professional remote work or school work, spaces for creating and playing, and several comfortable gathering spots. The home meets so many different needs, including income generating via the separate guest suite. Entertaining is easy with a kitchen designed for real life: spacious quartz countertops, ample serving spaces, and brand new double ovens. The kitchen flows into the dining room in one direction, and to the living room and breakfast room in the other, making it a true hub of the home. A favorite feature of the built-in desk area is that it overlooks the front yard and driveway--perfect for seeing kids returning from school or visitors arriving. 

Illahee Hills is a highly desirable neighborhood; homes are rarely on the market. The neighborhood has a mix of ages, from toddlers and elementary kids to adults of all ages and stages of life. The location can't be beat; it's less than a mile to the high school and walking distance to downtown Brevard. Biking, hiking, and camping are huge draws; the two forests that border the town and area offer some of the best trails and fly fishing anywhere.
